7)**\nAfter `session list --json`, the agent already has the chosen entry's metadata. But Step 2 still runs `entire session info <id> --transcript`. If `session current --transcript` (or piping `session list` directly to filter+stream) carries the metadata inline, we save a round-trip. **Fix:** when the shortcut path is taken, do `entire session current --transcript > /tmp/...` as the single command — metadata for the summary can come from the JSONL header, no separate `--json` call needed.\n\n**3. Step 3 — three greps over the same file on the long-file branch (lines 79–87)**\nOn the >500-line path, the file is grepped three times: once implicitly (to count), then `tail -100`, then `head -20`. On a multi-MB transcript that's ~3x the I/O. **Fix:** single pass — `grep -E '...' file | tee >(head -20 > /tmp/h) | tail -100 > /tmp/t`, or just always do `head -20 && tail -100` and skip the size check entirely (the threshold check itself requires reading the file).\n\n**4. Hot-path bloat — `cut -c1-2000` per line is fine, but the size-check itself is wasteful (line 82)**\n\"If the filtered output exceeds ~500 lines\" implies counting first. **Fix:** drop the conditional; unconditionally use head+tail. The full-file branch is rarely the right call interactively.\n\n**5. Temp file is justified** for re-scanning (head + tail), so piping isn't a win there — keep `/tmp/handoff-<id>.jsonl`.\n\n**6. Step 5 of checkpoint flow (line 132)** runs `--json` after `--transcript` only \"if you need session counts.\" Good — already lazy. No change."}],"totalDurationMs":22377,"totalTokens":31038,"totalToolUseCount":1,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":15984,"cache_read_input_tokens":14198,"output_tokens":855,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":15984},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":855,"cache_read_input_