{"parentUuid":"ea262265-fcc6-4175-88b7-6feb5e505137","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01Aehja7QPAMwQu8UAhV7TZh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## How the skill works on this branch\n\n**Trigger.** Three shapes: `hand off this session`, `hand off the codex session`, or \"hand off checkpoint <id>\". The `description` frontmatter gates activation; everything else is in-skill logic.\n\n**Active session flow (default):**\n1. `entire session list --json` returns every session across all worktrees as a JSON array.\n2. The skill filters that array in-process: scope to current worktree (bidirectional prefix match between `cwd` and `worktree_path`, with an unscoped fallback), drop self-agent (the agent currently running the skill), apply optional user-named agent substring filter, sort by `last_active` desc, take first.\n3. `entire session info <id> --transcript > /tmp/handoff-<id>.jsonl` writes the raw agent-native transcript to disk (JSONL for most agents; one JSON document for Gemini CLI). The CLI handles snapshot bounds and partial-line trimming.\n4. Two `grep | cut | head -20` and `| tail -100` invocations extract conversation lines (head = original task, tail = final state). Gemini CLI is read with the Read tool instead.\n5. Five-section compaction summary (Task Overview → Current State → Important Discoveries → Next Steps → Context to Preserve), plus an \"Unanswered Question\" section if the prior agent's last turn asked the user something.\n6. Show summary; if there's an unanswered question, route it to the user; otherwise keep working.\n\n**Checkpoint flow:**\n1. `entire checkpoint explain <id> --json` — read the `sessions` array length.\n2. If 1 session: `--transcript` (V2 normalized compact). If >1: iterate `--raw-transcript --session-index N` for each index. The branch is the bug fix from Codex review — the `--transcript` default is \"latest session only\".\n3. Same five-section summary; earlier sessions feed Discoveries/Context, latest feeds State/Next Steps.\n\n**Output contract.** First response gets a `Entire Session Handoff:` header line; error/early-exit responses don't. Skill is allowed to run `entire` commands plus shell pipelines on their output; no `git log/status/branch`, no globbing `.git/`.\n\n## Where it could still be improved\n\nThese are real gaps, not /simplify nits — pick what's worth fixing:\n\n1. **Prefix-match heuristic is fragile across symlinks and `/private/var` vs `/var` macOS quirks.** A cleaner solve: use `entire session current --json` to get the canonical `worktree_path` once, then filter `session list --json` against that. Two CLI calls instead of one, but no `cwd`-format guessing. Trade-off: extra round trip; benefit: deterministic.\n\n2. **No deduplication when self-filter empties the list.** If only the skill's own agent is in this worktree (common: I run handoff in the same Claude Code session that did the work), the skill prints \"nothing to hand off\" — but the user's actual intent was probably \"summarize *my* current session for compaction.\" Worth deciding: should self be a hard exclude, or should it be a soft preference that falls back to self if there's no other choice? Right now it's a hard exclude.\n\n3. **Multi-session checkpoint Step 2 doesn't bound work.** If a checkpoint has 50 sessions, the skill writes 50 temp files and runs 100 grep commands. In practice checkpoints rarely have >5 sessions, but there's no upper bound or \"recent N only\" cap. Worth adding \"if `sessions.length > 8`, take the last 8 by timestamp.\"\n\n4. **Gemini CLI branch is under-specified.** The skill says \"read the file with the Read tool and locate the messages / contents array\" — that's vague enough that different agents will produce different summaries. If we want Gemini parity, we need to name the actual JSON key paths.\n\n5. **`/tmp/handoff-<id>.jsonl` is never cleaned up.** Not a security issue (transcripts already live in user-trusted paths), but stale files accumulate. A `trap rm` or pre-write cleanup would be tidy.\n\n6. **No verification that the picked session is actually handoffable.** A `status: \"ended\"` session months old will pass all filters and become \"the most recent.\" Worth filtering to `status == \"active\"` or sessions with `last_active` within a sane window (e.g. last 24h) — at minimum, surface the staleness in the summary header.\n\n7. **The five-section format is rigid.** For very short sessions (\"the agent did one bug fix\"), Discoveries/Context-to-Preserve will be empty and the agent often hallucinates content to fill them. A note like \"omit empty sections\" would help.\n\n8. **No way to inspect *which* session was chosen.** When the filter picks the wrong session, the user has no signal — the skill jumps straight to summary. A one-line \"handing off `<agent>` session from <last_active>, <turns> turns\" before the summary would let the user catch a wrong pick early.\n\nWhich of these (if any) do you want to address? #2, #6, and #8 feel like the highest-value ones; #1 is a real correctness gap but #2/#6 have higher hit rates day-to-day."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":97912,"cache_read_input_tokens":18304,"output_tokens":1856,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":97912,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":6,"output_tokens":1856,"cache_read_input_tokens":18304,"cache_creation_input_tokens":97912,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":97912},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CaqhvH9C5fM6hVkU8XXY4","type":"assistant","uuid":"f8a64e42-9c90-4329-bec3-b9ce0711db09","timestamp":"2026-05-08T20:08:48.584Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/alisha/.marvin/